
[1]colander

   COLANDER, n. A vessel with a bottom perforated with little holes for
   straining liquors. In America, this name is given, I believe,
   exclusively to a vessel of tin, or other metal. In Great Britain, the
   name is given to vessels, like sieves, made with hair, osiers or twigs.
     __________________________________________________________________

